    ),
    LibraryCardModel(
      id: 'Library_Workout1_Card3',
      title: 'Evidence vs Interpretation',
      body: '“Meaning moves faster than proof.”\n\nEvidence is observable.\n\nInterpretation is added meaning.\n\nThe system can blend the two together automatically —\nunless awareness separates them.\n\nThis is where many reactions begin:\nnot with evidence,\nbut with interpretation sounding real.\n\nInterpretation says:\n‘Something must be wrong.’\n\nEvidence says:\n‘Not enough information exists yet.’\n\nInterpretation says:\n‘This means something.’\n\nEvidence says:\n‘That has not been confirmed.’\n\nInterpretation says:\n‘I already know what this means.’\n\nReality says:\n‘Meaning arrived before proof.’\n\nAwareness changes the timing.\n\nOnce interpretation becomes visible,\nautomatic belief weakens.\n\n***\n\nCore Rule:\n\n‘If proof is missing,\nmeaning already entered.’”',
