    ),
    LibraryCardModel(
      id: 'Library_Workout1_Card5',
      title: 'Why the Same Stories Return',
      body: '“Familiar meaning returns quickly.”\n\nYour system follows familiarity.\n\nNot certainty.\n\nIf an interpretation repeats enough times,\nit becomes easier to believe automatically.\n\nNot because it is true.\n\nBecause it became familiar.\n\nThe system learns through repetition:\n- repeated meaning\n- repeated assumptions\n- repeated conclusions\n- repeated interpretation\n\nEventually,\nfamiliarity starts sounding like certainty.\n\nThis is why the same stories can return:\neven when reality changes.\n\nAwareness changes this process.\n\nEach time interpretation becomes visible earlier,\nautomatic belief weakens.\n\nNew awareness creates new repetition.\n\nAnd new repetition changes what feels believable.\n\n‘Awareness changes what becomes believable.’”',
