final workout2LibraryModule = LibraryModuleModel(
  workoutIndex: 2,
  cards: [
    LibraryCardModel(
      id: 'Library_Workout2_Card1',
      title: 'What Is the Loop?',
      body: '“The same signal can get treated as new repeatedly.”\n\nA loop begins when a reaction becomes new input.\n\nOne signal appears.\n\nThen the system reacts.\n\nThen the reaction itself gets treated as confirmation.\n\nNothing new entered the system.\n\nThe same signal kept getting recycled.\n\nThis is why amplification can feel:\n- bigger\n- newer\n- more important\n- more convincing\n\n…even when the original signal did not change.\n\nLoops feel powerful because reinforcement feels like proof.\n\n***\n\nSignal:\n‘A sensation appeared.’\n\nReinforcement:\n‘The reaction must mean something important.’\n\nSignal:\n‘A thought appeared.’\n\nReinforcement:\n‘The response confirms it.’\n\n‘Awareness begins when reinforcement becomes visible.’”',
    ),
    LibraryCardModel(
      id: 'Library_Workout2_Card2',
      title: 'Why the Loop Feels Like Amplification',
      body: '“Repetition can feel like escalation.”\n\nThe loop does not require something new to happen.\n\nIt only requires the same signal\nto keep getting reinforced.\n\nThis is why:\n- checking strengthens repetition\n- monitoring keeps loops active\n- reacting creates more reaction\n- responses become new input\n\nThe system can mistake repetition for importance.\n\nAnd once reinforcement begins,\namplification can feel convincing very quickly.\n\nNot because the signal changed.\n\nBecause the loop kept feeding itself.\n\n‘The same signal can sound new when reinforcement repeats it.’”',
    ),
    LibraryCardModel(
      id: 'Library_Workout2_Card3',
      title: 'The Reinforcement Point',
      body: '“The loop grows where reaction becomes confirmation.”\n\nThe reinforcement point is where the system starts feeding itself.\n\nA signal appears.\n\nThen a reaction appears.\n\nThen the reaction gets interpreted as:\n- proof\n- confirmation\n- urgency\n- importance\n\nThat is where amplification begins.\n\nNot at the first signal.\n\nAt the moment the response becomes new evidence.\n\nThis is why awareness matters.\n\nOnce reinforcement becomes visible,\ninterruption becomes possible.\n\n***\n\nCore Rule:\n\n‘The loop strengthens when reactions become new input.’”',
    ),
    LibraryCardModel(
      id: 'Library_Workout2_Card4',
      title: 'Why Checking Strengthens the Loop',
      body: '“Monitoring can become reinforcement.”\n\nChecking often feels useful.\n\nBut repeated checking can teach the system:\n‘Keep this signal active.’\n\nThis is how:\n- monitoring becomes fuel\n- reassurance seeking becomes repetition\n- repeated attention strengthens loops\n\nNothing new needs to happen.\n\nThe same signal only needs:\nmore reinforcement.\n\nChecking can accidentally recycle the same signal again and again.\n\nThis is why loops can feel persistent:\nthe system keeps receiving the same input repeatedly.\n\n‘Repeated checking can become repeated reinforcement.’”',
    ),
    LibraryCardModel(
      id: 'Library_Workout2_Card5',
      title: 'What Weakens the Loop',
      body: '“Loops weaken when reinforcement stops.”\n\nA loop loses strength when the system stops recycling the same signal.\n\nNot because the first signal disappears.\n\nBecause reinforcement stops feeding it.\n\nThis is why visibility matters.\n\nOnce awareness notices:\n- reinforcement\n- repeated checking\n- recursive reactions\n- repeated confirmation\n- loops feeding themselves\n\n…the structure becomes interruptible.\n\nThe goal is not controlling signals.\n\nThe goal is detecting reinforcement earlier.\n\nNew awareness changes what gets repeated.\n\nAnd what stops repeating\nstops strengthening automatically.\n\n‘Visibility changes what gets reinforced.’”',
    ),
  ],
);

final workout3LibraryModule = LibraryModuleModel(
