    ),
    LibraryCardModel(
      id: 'Library_Workout3_Card5',
      title: 'How the System Learns Something New',
      body: '“The system updates through repetition.”\n\n“The sequence changes through repeated non-obedience.\n\nA signal appears.\n\nThe instruction follows.\n\nBut the obedience does not complete automatically.\n\nThat is the training.\n\nOver time,\nthe system begins learning:\n- signals can exist without reaction\n- sensations can exist without automatic obedience\n- the next move is not always required\n\nThis is not suppression.\n\nAnd it is not calming.\n\nIt is sequence retraining through awareness.\n\nNothing needs forcing.\n\nThe signal can remain.\n\nThe sequence can still change.\n\n‘Awareness changes automatic obedience.’”',
    ),
  ],
);

